6:
Hm... What to do... My reputation as
a man is at stake here!
10:
Could he be any more obvious? If he
wants help, he can just ask...
20: Alk! Buddy, pal! I'm glad you asked!
23:
You see, I'm trying to decide on a gift
for my beloved.
26:
Any ideas? I need something that
will make her really swoon.
30:
Uh... I mean, I don't know this person,
so I can't really say...
34:
Oh, don't worry about that. I don't
really "know" her either.
38:
Huh? Then how is she your beloved?
Wait... Are you just making her up?
43:
No, no, no. My beloved is just very
shy. She'd never tell me what she
wants outright.
48:
So quit stalking her then. We ain't
bailing you out when you get
caught.
53:
Do I LOOK like the kind of person who
would stalk someone?! Surely you
don't think THAT lowly of me!
58:
On a serious note, I doubt any of us
would be helpful when it comes to
romantic gifts...
63:
Hm... If you don't know what she
wants, maybe focus on what you'd
personally like to give her instead.
67: What I want to give her, huh...
71:
That's it! A tiara! And I've got just the
one in mind too!
76:
Uh-oh, I've got a bad feeling about
this...
81:
That settles it! Looks like we're going
tiara shopping!
87:
Shopping, my ass! This is goddamn
theft!
90:
They may be corsairs themselves,
but stealing is still stealing!
94:
Don't get it twisted, boys. These
pirates were the ones who stole the
tiara from me.
99:
These thieves challenged me to a
fight, with the treasure on the line. It
sounded like fun, so I went along
with it...
102:
But then they snuck off with the
treasure while I was distracted!
107:
Dammit... Now I'm mad all over
again!
113:
This time, revenge will be mine!
Haha, come on, let's show these
thieves what we're made of!
116:
M-Marcus?! You DARE to show your
face on OUR ship?!  We'll make you
walk the plank for this!
119:
Dammit, why can't we ever have a
trouble-free adventure with you?!
123:
Come on, I'll make it worth your
while later, okay?
126:
I'm going after their captain! You
guys deal with these small fries!
130:
All right, but you OWE us! Don't you
dare forget!
135:
Hey, I'm here for my tiara. Hand it
over, and nobody gets hurt!
138:
Nobody gets hurt, my foot! You lot
have torn up my entire ship!
Considering all the trouble you
caused, I should just keep the damn
tiara!
141:
Urk... Still a top-notch fighter, I see...
But it doesn't matter! Your life ends
here!
143:
Gahahaha! Top-notch or not, even
YOU can't take on an army by
yourself!
147:
...You're right. Which is why I'm not
going to!
158:
Strange, isn't it? Thought I'd be a
lone wolf forever, but here we are.
161:
W-well... You're still outnumbered!
You won't escape your fate this
time! Get 'em, boys!
167:
That takes care of them... Thanks for
your help.
171:
Yeah, yeah. Don't try to smooth talk
your way outta this one.
175:
Come on now, there's no need to be
upset. These pirates have one heck
of a bounty on their heads. Turning
them in will net you a profit for sure.
180:
Is this what you meant by making it
worth our while?
184: So this is your beloved, huh?
187:
The sea goddess... That certainly
sounds like Marcus' type.
192: So she was just made-up after all.
201:
I owe my life to the goddess... And it
was about time I paid her back.
210:
Oh my! Who would abandon a poor
little baby here of all places? There,
there, little one...
212:
You know... Maybe the little tyke's the
son of the sea goddess. He might
just have her blessing!
217:
Well... My business here is done.
Time to get going.
225:
An old ship's log that I bought on the
black market. The merchant said it
was left behind by one of the great
Captain Jacques' henchmen.
228:
And some of these pages reek of
treasure! I can tell this baby'll lead
us to the mother lode!
233:
"Us"? Nope. Sorry. You're on your own
for this one.
238:
Huh? Why? I thought you said letting
me go alone was irresponsible!
242:
Well... I guess we need to let you
take SOME responsibility.
246:
Aw, don't be like that! We're talking
buried treasure here! It's almost
guaranteed to be a thrilling
adventure! Hey! Come on!
